  • Constructor Details

    • Node

      public Node()
      Constructs an empty node whose head and tail are both null.

    • Node

      private Node​(int current, T... inputs)
      Private constructor that implements the creation of a list from a variable number of arguments. If the end of the varargs have been reached, the tail of the node being constructed is set to null.
      Parameters:
      current - current index of varargs, incremented with each recursive call.
      inputs - varargs treated as an array to be converted to a list.

    • Node

      public Node​(T... inputs)
      Public interface for calling the private varargs constructor.
      Parameters:
      inputs - varargs to be converted to a list.

  • Method Details

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns an incomplete string representation of the list containing this node. For example, if the current node contains the Integer 5 and points to a node containing the Integer 6 which points to null, the output is "5, 6]". This is because this method exists solely to be called by the toString method implemented for the LinkedList<T> class.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      an incomplete string representation of this node and those that follow.
